Sec. 41.084. INCREASE OF ASSESSMENT. At any biennial board
election, the board may submit to the voters a proposition to
increase the maximum rate of assessment. The proposition is approved
and the new maximum rate is in effect if two-thirds or more of those
voting vote in favor of the proposition or if those voting in favor
of the proposition produced at least 50 percent of the volume of
production of the commodity during the relevant production period.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1089, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

